Portions of this package's test data and source are derived from MoSQITo
(https://github.com/Eomys/MoSQITo), licensed under the Apache License 2.0
(see LICENSE-MoSQITo in this directory):

- test/data/din45692_band_levels.jl: 28-band levels computed from the
  DIN 45692:2009 chapter-6 test signals vendored by MoSQITo; reference
  sharpness values transcribed from
  validations/sq_metrics/sharpness_din/validation_sharpness_din.py.
- test/data/mosqito_crosscheck.jl: expected values computed by running
  MoSQITo's sharpness_din_from_loudness.
- src/weighting_fastl.jl: weighting table transcribed from
  mosqito/sq_metrics/sharpness/sharpness_din/_weighting_fastl.py.
- test/data/dw_fig3_references.jl: Zwicker & Fastl roughness reference
  values from validations/sq_metrics/roughness_dw/input/references.py
  (MoSQITo commit d990c33f94f1).
- test/data/mosqito_roughness_crosscheck.jl: expected values computed by
  running MoSQITo's roughness_dw.
- src/bark.jl, src/roughness_dw_tables.jl: conversion and weighting tables
  transcribed from mosqito/utils and
  mosqito/sq_metrics/roughness/roughness_dw (MoSQITo commit d990c33f94f1).
- test/support/am_generator.jl: transcribed from
  mosqito/utils/am_sine_generator.py.
- src/roughness_dw.jl: transcribed from
  mosqito/sq_metrics/roughness/roughness_dw/_roughness_dw_main_calc.py,
  sound_level_meter/comp_spectrum.py and utils/time_segmentation.py
  (MoSQITo commit d990c33f94f1).

Portions of this package's test data and source reference SQAT
(https://github.com/ggrecow/SQAT), licensed under CC BY-NC 4.0, and the
model of Osses, García & Kohlrausch (2016), doi:10.1121/2.0000410, as
described in A. Osses Vecchi's PhD thesis (TU/e, 2018), Appendix B. No
SQAT source code, audio, or other CC BY-NC-licensed material is
reproduced or redistributed by this package; only numeric behavioral
facts (parameter values, computed outputs) are used:

- src/fluctuation_strength_tables.jl,
  src/fluctuation_strength_fir.jl: numeric parameter values (gzi and a0
  interpolation knots, hearing threshold knots, elliptic filter SOS
  coefficients, FIR design inputs) read from SQAT commit 00b449e
  (FluctuationStrength_Osses2016.m, calculate_a0.m,
  TerhardtExcitationPatterns.m, Get_Hweight_fluctuation.m and the
  Hweight-*.mat files).
- test/data/sqat_fs_crosscheck.jl: expected values computed by running
  SQAT's FluctuationStrength_Osses2016 (commit
  00b449e40599f1c1ef4abe0596094552213d57eb) under GNU Octave 11.3.0
  (octave-signal 1.4.7) on signals synthesized entirely by this
  package's own test generator (test/support/fs_stimuli.jl) — a numeric
  cross-check fixture, not transcribed code.

Portions of this package's test data and source reference SQAT
(https://github.com/ggrecow/SQAT), licensed under CC BY-NC 4.0, and
the model of Widmann (1992, doctoral thesis, TU München; formula
p. 66), identified per Lotinga & Torija (2025), JASA 157(5):3282-
3285. No SQAT source code, audio, or other CC BY-NC-licensed
material is reproduced or redistributed by this package; only
numeric behavioral facts (formula constants, computed outputs) are
used:

- src/psychoacoustic_annoyance.jl: formula constants (the S > 1.75
  threshold, 2.18, the 0.4/0.6 weights, N^0.4, log10(N+10)/4) read
  from SQAT commit 00b449e
  (PsychoacousticAnnoyance_Widmann1992_from_percentile.m); the
  Inf/NaN-zeroing construct is likewise cited as a structural fact,
  not transcribed code.
- test/data/sqat_pa_crosscheck.jl: expected values computed by
  running SQAT commit 00b449e40599f1c1ef4abe0596094552213d57eb, both
  PsychoacousticAnnoyance_Widmann1992_from_percentile.m (840-case
  formula grid) and the signal-level
  PsychoacousticAnnoyance_Widmann1992.m (4 cases, vendoring PA plus
  SQAT's own N5/S5/R5/FS5 percentile values), under GNU Octave 11.3.0
  (octave-signal 1.4.7) on signals synthesized entirely by this
  package's own test generator (test/support/fs_stimuli.jl) —
  numeric, values-only cross-check fixtures, not transcribed code.
